==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water pore
<hw>Wa"ter pore`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A pore by which the water tubes of various invertebrates open
externally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of certain minute pores in the
leaves of some plants. They are without true guardian cells, but in
other respects closely resemble ordinary stomata.</def>
<rj><au>Goodale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waterpot</ent>⟦br⟧
